To find the common elements in set A and set B, we first list out the multiples of 3 between 10 and 30, inclusive, and the multiples of 4 between 5 and 25, inclusive.

Set A (multiples of 3 between 10 and 30, inclusive): {12, 15, 18, 21, 24, 27, 30}
Set B (multiples of 4 between 5 and 25, inclusive): {8, 12, 16, 20, 24}

Now, we find the common elements in both sets:

Common elements: {12, 24}

Thus, the set of all common elements in set A and set B is {12, 24}.
